    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>den 9<hi rend="sup">th</hi> July 1854</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <sic>
                    <addressee>Rev: Mr Isaack Leeser</addressee>
                </sic>
            </p>
            <p>
                <add>Hebrew</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <persName role="author">Nathan Ottinger</persName>
            </p>
            <p><placeName>161 Division St</placeName>:</p>
            <pb n="Envelope"/>
            <p>
                <sic>
                    <addressee>Rev: Isaack Leeser</addressee>
                </sic>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>. <date>July 9<hi rend="sup"
                        >th</hi>, 1854</date></p>
            <p>
                <add>Yiddish</add>
            </p>
            <p><sic><addressee>Rev. Mr. Isaack Leeser</addressee></sic>,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">If you should by chance send any-<lb/>thing to <placeName>New
                    York</placeName>, or if you can indicate<lb/> some place here where I can get
                them,<lb/> I need several Portuguese prayer-books,<lb/> leather-bound, and several
                Dibrei<lb/> Zadikim* (Words of the Wise) unbound<lb/> I hoped to be able to speak to
                you, since<lb/> you <del>were</del> have been here on several occasions, but<lb/> to
                my great regret I did not have the<lb/> honor. I also wanted that you should<lb/>
                recommend me in the Occident that<lb/> I have a <del>great</del> large collection of
                all<lb/> kinds of books; Talmud, Mishnah,<lb/> Holiday prayer-books, also
                prayer<lb/> books of German and of Polish Minhag,<lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">as well as some scrolls</hi> of the Torah.</p>
            <p>* Probably name of a Prayer-Book</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>You know best how to put the advertise-<lb/>ment together. I shall again
                regulate<lb/> my debts. Should I again receive<lb/> Ethrogin from
                    <placeName>Italy</placeName>. I shall let you<lb/> know, and should you need
                some<lb/> again. I am ever at your service</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Your friend,</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Nathan Ottinger</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <placeName>161 Division St.</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
